    "notes": "50kg Humanoid, mountains walker, #App: 4d6, Treasure: Small. Swords (2d6), Bows (2d6); armor 3; speed 10m/action; Morale -1. Small (70-100cm tall) green-skinned humanoids that live as bandits and scavengers in human lands. They have their own tribes and civilizations in wilder environs. Goblins are excellent at ambushes, and should never be underestimated. If encountered in the wilderness, Goblins might have 2d6 dire wolves which they ride as mounts. A group of goblins encountered in a dungeon might have a Large treasure in a lair nearby, and only Incidental treasure on them.",
